---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import ConvertFormat from '../../components/tools/ConvertFormat';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Convert HEIC to JPG Free Online | Filekrush"
  description="Convert iPhone HEIC photos to JPG instantly. Runs in your browser — no upload, no signup."
  canonical="/convert/heic-to-jpg"
  heading="Convert HEIC to JPG"
  subheading="Convert iPhone photos to JPG — free, private, instant."
>
  <ConvertFormat client:only="react" fromFormat="image/heic" toFormat="image/jpeg" />

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <section class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
      <h2>What is HEIC?</h2>
      <p>HEIC (High Efficiency Image Container) is the default photo format on iPhones and iPads. It produces smaller files than JPG at the same quality, but many websites, apps, and Windows PCs cannot open HEIC files.</p>

      <h2>Why convert to JPG?</h2>
      <p>JPG is universally supported. Converting HEIC to JPG ensures your photos work everywhere — email attachments, online forms, social media, Windows computers, and web uploads.</p>

      <h2>Is it safe?</h2>
      <p>Yes. Your photos are converted entirely in your browser. Nothing is uploaded to any server. The HEIC file never leaves your device.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</ToolLayout>
